content:
The Compare Table's function menu provides UI-based access to useful window functions, saving you the time of having to write them in SAQL. Once you choose a function, you can edit the generated SAQL in the formula editor.

Available window functions include:

* Sliding Window: applies an aggregate function to the current row with respect to a configurable range of rows.
* Percentage of Group: calculates the percentage each row is of its group total or grand total.
* Rank Within Group: provides rank, dense rank, cumulative distribution, and row-number functions.
* Period Over Period: compares periods of time to calculate changes in values.
* Change from Previous: compares the value of the current row with that of the previous row and calculates the difference.
* Running Total: calculates the total value of the current row summed with all previous rows.
title: Understanding Window Functions in Salesforce Analytics
